<% @title = 'Marketing Automation With SiteFoil' %>
<% @description = 'Add a layer of personalization to your website using powerful scheduling tools.' %>

<h1>Website Marketing Personalization </h1>

<p>The following lists of available triggers and actions was last updated on December 7, 2014</p>
<p>For additional channels, triggers, or actions, please <%= link_to ('let us know'), new_contact_path %> what you would like to see added.</p>

<hr />
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-6">
<h2>Available Triggers</h2>
	<ul style="margin:0px; padding:0px;">
		<li style="list-style-type:none;"><h3><div class="rounded-box">  
                                        <span class="glyphicon fa fa-money big-glyphicon text-center" style="margin:auto;"></span>
                                    </div>E-Commerce Triggers</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Conversion Rate (%)</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on your site's current all-time conversion rate.</li>
				<li><strong>Conversion Rate (%) last 24 hours</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on your site's current 24-hour trailing conversion rate.</li>
				<li><strong>Transactions</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on your site's current all-time number of transactions.</li>
			</ul></li>
		<li style="list-style-type:none;"><h3><div class="rounded-box">  
                                         <span class="glyphicon fa fa-users big-glyphicon text-center" style="margin:auto;"></span>
                                    </div>Site Visitor Triggers</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Country</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on a visitor's country</li>
				<li><strong>IP Address</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on a visitor's ip address</li>
				<li><strong>Language</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on a visitor's language</li>
				<li><strong>Operating System</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on a visitor's operating system</li>
				<li><strong>Platform</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on a visitor's platform</li>
				<li><strong>Referrer</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on the URL where a visitor comes from</li>
				<li><strong>Visitor Type</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on whether the visitor is new or returning</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li style="list-style-type:none;"><h3><div class="rounded-box">
                                        <span class="glyphicon fa fa-calendar big-glyphicon text-center" style="margin:auto;"></span>
                                    </div>Date/Time Triggers</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Date</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on the current date </li>
				<li><strong>Hour</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on the current hour </li>
				<li><strong>Hours:minutes</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on the current hour & minute </li>
				<li><strong>Weekday number</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on the current weekday</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li style="list-style-type:none;"><h3><div class="rounded-box">   
                                        <span class="glyphicon fa fa-location-arrow big-glyphicon text-center" style="margin:auto;"></span>
                                    </div>Site Triggers</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Element clicked ID</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on what is clicked on your site </li>
				<li><strong>Page URL</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on what URL is visited </li>
				<li><strong>Page Visited</strong> <br /> trigger an action based on what page is visited </li>
			</ul>
		</li>
	</ul>


</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
